If you look at the source for that example, he actually has 2 selectors that set an item to red, corresponding to the 3rd item in a group of 5 and the 7th item in a group of 9 (Formatted here for legibility):<p><pre><code>    span:nth-child(3):nth-last-child(3){
        background-color:red !important;
    }

    span:nth-child(7):nth-last-child(3){
        background-color:red !important;
    }
</code></pre>
That threw me for a bit of a loop too. &quot;Wait, is that second item supposed to be red?&quot; It would be clearer if the example and the demo matched up.
